Ad Text:
Talent International is currently recruiting for a Senior People Insights Analyst, based in Kensington. This position is a contract role for 4 months initially, with the view to be extended and pays an hourly rate of $70 to $75 per hour + Super.

7 hours a day / 35 hours per week

You'll play a critical role in designing and delivering reporting frameworks, dashboards, and workforce insights that enable data-driven decisions across People & Culture (P&C). This is a hands-on role requiring advanced analytics skills and the ability to translate data into meaningful business outcomes.

Key Responsibilities:

Extract and analyse people data using SQL and PeopleSoft.
Develop and maintain dashboards/reports to ensure compliance with legislation, policies, and enterprise agreements.
Partner with stakeholders to translate business requirements into actionable insights.
Deliver analytics and workforce trends that inform strategic decision-making.
Provide documentation, mentoring, and support to enhance reporting capability across P&C.
Ensure data integrity, governance, and compliance.

About You:

Strong experience in Advanced SQL, PeopleSoft experience - main HRIS, and data visualisation tools (Power BI preferred).
Skilled in designing and implementing reporting frameworks in complex organisations.
Proven ability to translate data into strategic workforce insights.
Exceptional communication skills, with the ability to engage technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Experience with Databricks and Azure DevOps (desirable).
Strong problem-solving, documentation, and project coordination skills.

What's in it for you?

Work with a prestigious university in a pivotal analytics role.
Contribute to workforce strategy and data transformation initiatives.
Hybrid working flexibility (Kensington office + WFH).
Contract with the potential to extend.

If you're a data-driven professional with strong PeopleSoft and SQL expertise, we'd love to hear from you.

If you are interested in this role, please APPLY NOW by submitting your resume in MS Word Format. For further information, you may contact Uvez Ahmed on 02 8240 9596 / uvez.ahmed@talentinternational.com for a confidential discussion.

About the Role

This role will co-design and test optimised complaints and assessment processes, mapping new workflows, integrating existing processes, quantifying benefits, and updating procedures following a recent review and 2-year implementation plan.

Responsibilities:

Lead the mapping, design, and refinement of complaints and assessment processes.
Collaborate with stakeholders to understand current practices and identify improvement opportunities.
Develop future-state process maps, functional models, and service delivery models.
Support creation of procedures and training guides.
Quantify benefits of process improvements using data and performance metrics.

About You:

Proven experience leading process improvement initiatives in complex environments, ideally as part of a transformation project (non-technical role).
Strong business analysis experience, ideally in government or highly regulated environments.
Experience with Lean Six Sigma, BABOK, PMBOK/Prince2, or BPM methodologies (Lean Six Sigma highly regarded).
Strong communication skills and ability to influence senior stakeholders.
Critical thinking, problem-solving, and data analysis capabilities.

The Company:

This organisation helps keep Victoria's public institutions honest and accountable. It investigates serious cases of corruption and police misconduct, and works to prevent them by educating government bodies, police, and the wider community. Its work covers state and local government, police, parliament, and the courts.

The Next Step:

To be successful, you must be willing to obtain a clear National Police Check.

HDI Global in Australia is represented by HDI Global SE, Australia and HDI Global Specialty SE – Australia. Both companies are headquartered in Sydney with Branch offices in Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. Our team of local and empowered underwriting experts in Australia provide a commercial and flexible underwriting approach, which allows us to consider innovative ideas across all lines of our general insurance business, distribution channels and markets.

HDI Global SE is Germany’s leading industrial insurer and has been servicing German and European companies in Australia and New Zealand since 1995. As an industrial lines insurer, HDI Global SE meets the needs of SMEs, industrial companies and corporate customers with insurance solutions that are specifically tailored to their requirements for Property, Construction, Casualty, Accident & Health, Marine, Cyber and Motor Fleet risk. The company also has operations in more than 175 countries through foreign branch offices, subsidiary companies, and network partners.

HDI Global Specialty SE is wholly owned by HDI Global, being a strong and established player in the insurance market. By housing the specialty activities of the Talanx Group in HDI Global Specialty SE (HSAB), we have created an excellent platform for putting together cross-business segment expertise and network reach.

Data Analyst

We are looking for a Data Analyst to join our Actuarial team. This role is ideal for someone with a sharp eye for detail, who enjoys problem-solving and is comfortable working with large volumes of data. You will play a key role in improving data quality, increasing efficiencies and communicating effectively between technical and non-technical stakeholders.

This is a critical role in turning complex information into clear, actionable insights to claims, underwriting, actuarial and management. This role offers a fantastic opportunity to enhance passion for data and analytics by obtaining visibility across the entire business. It demands and rewards individuals that are highly proactive with a solutions-focused mindset and strong communication skills.

Key Duties:

Develop and create data connections using SQL queries and DBT to extract, transform and load data from various source systems for use within the business.

Design and create processes to transform the raw data into clean, structured and analytics-ready datasets.

Design and create database management tools to collect and store underwriting, policy and claims data within local pricing tariffs and processing workbooks.

Design and create database management tools to collect and store all other local data sources such as local IBNR, Reinsurance arrangements, investment returns, master asset listings for accumulation and capital modelling etc.

Implement and maintain best practices for data modelling and data governance.

Power BI (live connections) and technical setup to extract data out of Policy and Claims Handling systems as well as financial ledger systems.

Includes extracting data out of CRM and Actuarial Pricing and Reserving systems in future environment.

Aid the Head of Operations with technical system feature rollouts within CRM and other potential projects.

Aid Finance in finding ways to combine, generate and extract data to automate statutory reporting requirements.

Skills and Experience:

Minimum 2 years’ experience working with data and/or related role within the financial services industry.

Bachelors Degree in Data Analytics, Statistics, Computer Science or related field.

Advanced Proficiency in MS Excel/VBA.

Proficiency in data analysis tools such as Python, R and/or SQL.

Proficiency in data visualisation platforms such as Power BI.

General Insurance Industry experience desired.

This is a great opportunity for a motivated, proactive and professional individual to join our Actuarial & Analytics team and meaningfully contribute to the continued growth of our Australian business.

HDI offers a values-based dynamic working environment, a flexible approach to work, and a learning framework to support your continued development. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals and believe that diversity and inclusion are critical to our future.

You will need to already have permanent rights to work in Australia (either citizen or permanent residency).

If you would like to become a member of the HDI team, please click on the apply now button.

Pacific Energy is an Australian market leader in the provision of sustainable distributed energy. Our purpose is to transition the world to a clean energy future.

As Australia’s only end-to-end provider of all renewable energy technologies, with proven experience integrating solar, wind, battery energy storage and green hydrogen into new and existing systems, we deliver industry firsts that are leading the clean energy transition.




Be the difference at Pacific Energy              

At Pacific Energy, we know that diverse backgrounds, industry expertise, and unique skill sets are the driving force behind innovation. We value diverse ideas, backgrounds and experience.
We’re on the lookout for a dynamic Senior HRIS Analyst to join our People, Culture & Sustainability team.

This is more than a technical role — it’s a chance to build the future of our HR systems, elevate data integrity, and deliver insights that shape how we support our people and organisation.

You will be reporting to the Senior Manager - HR Services.
This is a full time, permanent opportunity based in our Kewdale HQ office.

Why Join us

We value innovation and invest in our people with benefits that prioritise work-life balance and professional growth:

Fantastic opportunity to make a difference, add value and be valued.
Fantastic remuneration package
Enjoy flexible working arrangements including a nine-day fortnight option
Free on-site parking
17 weeks of paid parental leave for both primary & secondary carers
Health & wellness reimbursements
Salary sacrifice for super, vehicles, education
Ongoing career progression and much more!



BE part of the change

As our Senior HRIS Analyst, you’ll be the engine behind our systems excellence — leading initiatives that streamline operations, enhance user experience, and unlock smarter decision-making.

You will be responsible for:

System Administration and Maintenance, configuring, testing and maintaining our HRIS platforms.
Lead and support system implementation and enhancement projects.
Lead and coordinate change management initiatives by designing process maps, overseeing workflow optimisation, and developing concise quick reference materials to support seamless transitions.
Manage user access, permissions and security protocols.
Perform regular audits and data cleansing.

Build Power BI (or similar) dashboards and generate reports for HR metrics.
Identify inefficiencies in HR workflows and propose tech-driven solutions to maximise systems performance.
Champion innovation (including AI) and continuous improvement advancements.

BE part of the solution

Proven experience in HRIS platforms (Workday, SAP SuccessFactors, Elmo, etc.)
Qualifications in Data Science, Systems Management, or Human Resources desirable. 
Strong grasp of system integrations, data flows, and visualisation tools.
Advanced reporting and dashboard creation skills (Power BI or similar)
Analytical mindset with the ability to translate data into actionable outcomes.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills.

To be considered for this role, you must have permanent full working rights in Australia.

Job Title: Property Analyst - Debt Finance / Non-Bank Lending
Ad Text:
Property Analyst – Commercial Property Investment
South Melbourne, VIC | Flexible Work-from-Home Options

Are you ready to take your analytical skills to the next level in a high-impact role within a fast-paced, forward-thinking property investment firm?

Join a boutique investment powerhouse known for its strategic insight, collaborative culture, and innovative approach to real estate investment. Based in South Melbourne, this firm is redefining how property investment decisions are made—combining data-driven analysis with deep market expertise to deliver exceptional outcomes for clients.

The Opportunity
As a Property Analyst, you’ll be at the heart of the investment process—supporting strategic decisions, managing loan portfolios, and driving performance insights across a diverse range of property projects. This is a rare opportunity to work closely with senior leadership and gain exposure to high-value deals in a dynamic and entrepreneurial environment.

What You’ll Do
Conduct in-depth market research and financial modelling to assess property investment opportunities
Manage and track loan data, performance metrics, and monthly reporting
Prepare credit papers and Investment Committee submissions
Coordinate drawdowns and liaise with stakeholders across Melbourne and Brisbane
Monitor deal performance and maintain accurate, up-to-date records
Support due diligence and collaborate with internal teams and external consultants
Create investment memorandums, reports, and presentations for key stakeholders
What You Bring
A degree in Property, Finance, Economics, or a related field
2+ years of experience in property finance analysis, valuation, or investment (preferred)
Strong Excel skills and financial modelling capabilities
Familiarity with property research tools
Excellent communication skills and attention to detail
A proactive, self-starting attitude and a genuine interest in property markets
Why Join?
Work with a high-performing, close-knit team that values innovation and initiative
Enjoy flexible working arrangements and a supportive culture
Accelerate your career with exposure to complex deals and strategic decision-making
Access ongoing professional development and growth opportunities
The remuneration confirmed by my client is $120,000 - 160,000 + superannuation.

Ready to make your mark in property investment?
Apply now and be part of a firm where your insights drive real-world impact.

PSG are proud to be partnering with an ASX listed mining services that plays a critical role in keeping goods and services moving across Australia. With a rapidly growing customer base and a focus on innovation, they are investing heavily in their data capabilities to drive smarter decisions, optimise operations, and enhance customer experience.

As their recruitment partner, we are seeking a talented and driven Lead Data Analyst to head up a small but growing analytics team. This is a unique opportunity to step into a leadership role where you’ll be both hands-on with data and strategic in shaping the company’s data journey.

 
Key Responsibilities

Lead a team of data analysts, providing technical guidance, mentorship, and support.
Work closely with stakeholders to understand business requirements and translate them into actionable insights.
Develop and deliver data models, dashboards, and reports to support strategic decision-making.

Skills & Experience Required

Proven experience as a Senior or Lead Data Analyst (ideally within logistics, transport, supply chain, or a similar data-rich environment).
Strong technical proficiency in SQL and data visualisation tools such as Power BI or Tableau.

Solid understanding of data modelling, ETL processes, and analytics best practices.
Exceptional stakeholder management skills with the ability to communicate insights to both technical and non-technical audiences.

If you think this position suits you. Please apply or reach out directly to luke@psgaus.com.au
